main event: Several UFO sightings reported in Houston, Texas during March 1966, including sounds and visual observations of suspected unidentified flying objects.
interesting points: One sighting involved a humming sound that was heard, while the observer saw nothing, only various dogs barking., Observations included at least one light described as similar to Venus, confirmed to be a satellite., There was a report of a bright object hovering that seemed to emit colored lights and was estimated at relatively close proximity., Multiple reports were made for different dates, with some objects disappearing suddenly without explanation., One report indicated that an observer tried to report their sighting but was unable to complete the required forms in time.
sighted object: Various unidentified flying objects and lights in the sky, including one described as disc-shaped.
witness description: Witnesses described seeing various lights and objects in the sky, often emitting sounds and having bright colors.
